# runapp and restartall commands

When the user says **runapp**, **runall**, **reloadapp**, **rerunapp**, **restartall**, or **killAll**, do the following. **runall**, **reloadapp**, and **rerunapp** are aliases for **runapp**. The same rebuild-and-refresh procedure (run runapp script, then browser_tabs, then browser_navigate to open or refresh the app tab) is **mandatory after every feature and bug fix** — see the rule "post-feature-rebuild-and-refresh".

## Canonical port

**The app always runs on `http://localhost:3000`.** After runapp or restartall, open a Cursor Browser tab to that URL if none exists, or refresh the existing app tab to `http://localhost:3000?_=<timestamp>`. Never use 3001 or any other port.

## runapp

**Goal:** Build the app, start a dev server on port 3000 only if one isn't already running, and open or refresh a Cursor Browser tab to `http://localhost:3000`.

**runapp starts a new dev server only when necessary.** If port 3000 is already in use, the script only runs `npm run build` and leaves the existing server running. If port 3000 is free, it kills any process on 3000–3003, builds, then starts `npm run dev` on 3000. Use **restartall** when you want a full kill + rebuild + start (e.g. to fix asset hash mismatches).

The script:
1. If port 3000 is in use: runs `npm run build` only (no kill, no start).
2. If port 3000 is free: kills any process on 3000, 3001, 3002, 3003; waits briefly; runs `npm run build`; starts `npm run dev` on 3000.

**Do not reuse or navigate to port 3001, 3002, or 3003.**

1. Run `npm run runapp`, `npm run runall`, `npm run reloadapp`, or `npm run rerunapp`.
2. Wait 4–6 s for the dev server to be ready (if the script started a new one, it needs a moment; if one was already running, the wait is harmless).
3. **Open or refresh Cursor Browser on port 3000:** Call `browser_tabs` with `action: "list"`. If no tab has a URL containing `localhost:3000`, call `browser_navigate` with `http://localhost:3000?_=<timestamp>` and `newTab: true` to open a new Cursor Browser tab. If a tab already has the app (URL contains `localhost:3000`), call `browser_navigate` with `http://localhost:3000?_=<timestamp>` (no newTab) to refresh that tab. Always use the canonical port 3000 with a cache-busting query param.

## restartall

**Always** kills dev servers on 3000/3001, rebuilds, and starts fresh on 3000. Use when you want a full restart (e.g. after asset issues or to guarantee a clean server).

1. Run `npm run restartall` (kills all dev servers on 3000/3001/3002/3003, rebuilds, starts fresh on 3000).
2. Wait 4–6 s for the server to be ready.
3. **Open or refresh Cursor Browser:** Same as runapp — call `browser_tabs` (list); if no tab has `localhost:3000`, call `browser_navigate` with `newTab: true`; otherwise call `browser_navigate` to `http://localhost:3000?_=<timestamp>` to refresh.

## killAll

When the user says **killAll**, run `npm run killAll`. The script stops all processes on ports 3000, 3001, 3002, 3003 (dev servers started by Cursor). It does not build or start anything. No browser step.

## Summary

| Command     | Script does                          | Agent then                    |
|------------|---------------------------------------|-------------------------------|
| **runapp** / **runall** / **reloadapp** / **rerunapp** | Build always; start dev server on 3000 only if none running | Wait 4-6s; list tabs; open or refresh Cursor Browser to localhost:3000 |
| **restartall** | Always kill 3000/3001, build, start fresh on 3000 | Wait 4-6s; open or refresh Cursor Browser to localhost:3000 |
| **killAll** | Kill dev servers on 3000–3003 only (no build, no start) | None |
